<h1 class="title">Summary of Relativity</h1>
<p>
The "theoretical minimum" of relativity
</p>

<ol class="org-ol">
<li>You want the speed of light to be the same for all observers
a) EM says so
b) Determisim to depend on a finite past time slice
c) General transformations allow this possibility
d) Experiment !!!!</li>

<li>Implies the invariant is t<sup>2</sup> - x<sup>2</sup></li>
<li>This fixes the Lorentz transformations</li>
<li>Which fixes the additional of velocities</li>
<li>From this can figure out (with elastic collisions KE conserved) the definition of momentum such that it is conserved and reduces to mv with v - small</li>
<li>Here you recognize that this only 3 components of a four vector. Natural question: what is the 4th components</li>
<li>Lead directly to relativistic Energy = E=mÎ³ ~ mc<sup>2</sup> + 1/2mv<sup>2</sup> at low v
a) In particular rest mass E=mc<sup>2</sup></li>
<li>Look at in-elastic collisions KE not conserved, and discover rest mass is energy</li>
</ol>

